President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing Father's Day as a special occasion to honor fathers and their role in raising children. The proclamation acknowledges the love, sacrifices, and moral guidance that fathers provide, and encourages individuals, families, and communities to promote and support fatherhood. In accordance with a joint resolution of Congress, President Trump has designated June 18, 2017, as Father's Day, calling on government officials to display the flag of the United States on all government buildings and inviting the people of the United States to observe Father's Day with appropriate ceremonies.